  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Information Grant 2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Information projects 14,3 million DKK 
2) Administrative costs DKK 1,7 million 
3) World image grant DKK 1,3 million 

(1) Subsidy for information projects, including educational materials, to the general Danish population on conditions in emerging and developing countries. 2-3 application rounds per year. All projects above DKK 50.000 are assessed by the Committee. Projects under 50.000 can be assessed at secretarial level. 

(2) Administration, operation and development of the Information Pool, including costs for the external committee (fees), expenses related to committee meetings, IT expenses including licence for TAS.

(3) student video competition for travel grants to a growing or developing country. The World Image was not held in 2020 pga. COVID-19. The contest was projet externally (Buchs A/S). The framework for communicating to the Danish population is the SDGs. A prerequisite for support is that the destinations and the country (ies) targeted by an information project are in line with the DAC list.</narrative>
  </description>
